            <title>[FLUME-2157] Spool directory source does not shut down correctly when Flume is reconfigured</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-2157</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spool directory source does not shut down correctly when Flume is reconfigured. This can lead to all sorts of problems stemming from the fact that we have threads running which should not be. In the logs, it looks like multiple spool directory sources are running on the same directory, even though the config may say otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
